{
  "texts": [
    "Table 13 shows the prompts used for prompt-keywords, with keywords that appear in the questionnaire shown in bold.",
    "Figure 3 presents the BFI and IPIP-NEO test score results for the LLaMA-3 Instruct models, evaluated in zero-shot inference without any induced personality traits.",
    "The crowdsourced response scores for the BFI test are sourced from Huang et al. (2024), and those for the IPIP-NEO test are drawn from Jiang et al. (2023a).",
    "The results indicate that the scores for both LLaMA-3-8B-Instruct and LLaMA-3-70B-Instruct fall within the standard deviation of the human distribution.",
    "However, while LLaMA-3-8B-Instruct tends to generate more neutral scores (around 3 across most of the Big Five traits), LLaMA-3-70B-Instruct exhibits higher scores for openness, conscientiousness, extraversion, and agreeableness, and lower scores for neuroticism."
  ]
}